<subSubSection box="[199,989,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,646]" box="[199,989,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after the late James E. Wappes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="404" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,646]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Santos-Silva, 2022" authorityName="Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[323,506,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wappesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,506,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Bebelis wappesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[514,605,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[514,605,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Belon, 1903)" baseAuthorityName="Belon" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[756,1047,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[756,882,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">B. modesta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Belon, P. M." box="[898,1039,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" pagination="47 - 76" refId="ref18989" refString="Belon, P. M. (1903) Materiaux pour l'etude des longicornes de Bolivie. Revue d'Entomologie, 22, 47 - 76." type="journal article" year="1903">Belon, 1903</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1063,1166,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Figs 6–8</figureCitation>
), but differs as follows: body proportionally stouter (
<figureCitation box="[470,534,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,679,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-232@3.[151,1436,669,1954]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Bebelis wappesi sp. nov. 1–4) Holotype female: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Head, frontal view. 5) Paratype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886402/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); prothorax proportionally wider (
<figureCitation box="[918,982,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,679,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-232@3.[151,1436,669,1954]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Bebelis wappesi sp. nov. 1–4) Holotype female: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Head, frontal view. 5) Paratype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886402/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); elytra with distinct longitudinal pubescent bands in addition to the white band (
<figureCitation box="[620,722,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,679,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-232@3.[151,1436,669,1954]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Bebelis wappesi sp. nov. 1–4) Holotype female: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Head, frontal view. 5) Paratype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886402/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Figs 1, 5</figureCitation>
); mesanepisternum with abundant coarse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1322,1391,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Belon" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[151,275,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[151,275,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">B. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the body is proportionally slender (
<figureCitation box="[682,750,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), prothorax proportionally narrower (
<figureCitation box="[1170,1238,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), elytra only with the white longitudinal pubescent band, and mesanepisternum with sparse coarse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1166,1234,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson, 1864" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[293,591,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lignosa">
<emphasis box="[293,407,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">B. lignosa</emphasis>
Thomson, 1864
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[607,690,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bates, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[712,995,511,538]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coenosa">
<emphasis box="[712,836,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">B. coenosa</emphasis>
(Bates, 1866)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1011,1093,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bates, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1163,1436,511,538]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occulta">
<emphasis box="[1163,1277,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">B. occulta</emphasis>
(Bates, 1866)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[160,240,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) especially by the oblique anterior area of the central band of the elytra (including the white pubescent band and the yellowish-brown pubescent band starting on humerus) not reaching the suture (reaching the suture in these three species).
</paragraph>
